cryfa
------------------------------------------
Cryfa is an ultrafast secure encryption tool for genomic data, that is also
able to compact FASTA/FASTQ sequences by a factor of three.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libcryptopp8.6-8.6.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libcryptopp-devel-8.6.0-1bl1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/cobilab/cryfa

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/cobilab/cryfa/archive/refs/tags/v26.05.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cryfa-26.05-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cryfa-26.05-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cryfa-26.05-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cryfa-26.05-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(cryfa)
  /usr/bin/cryfa-keygen.exe
  /usr/bin/cryfa.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/cryfa.README
  /usr/share/doc/cryfa/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/cryfa/README.md

